  "title": "SHAWQ Programme Coordinator (2-Years Contract)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>About the Role</strong></u></p><p>The Programme Coordinator supports the coordination and administration of Al-Quran programmes, including ongoing classes and short courses. The role works closely with trainers, students, and parents to ensure programmes are delivered smoothly and professionally.</p><p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Coordinate and support the delivery of Al-Quran classes and short courses</li><li>Manage programme schedules, registrations, logistics, and resources</li><li>Handle programme-related communications with trainers, students and parents</li><li>Maintain programme records, reports, calendars, and administrative documentation</li><li>Support publicity materials, feedback collection, and special programmes when required</li><li>Carry out other administrative or operational duties as assigned</li></ul><p><br /><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><p><strong>Education & Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum NITEC in Business Administration, or</li><li>Equivalent relevant working experience</li></ul><p><strong>Skills & Competencies</strong></p><ul><li>Good organisational and coordination skills</li><li>Strong administrative skills with attention to detail</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint</li><li>Familiarity with digital tools (e.g., Canva, Google Forms, basic data tracking systems) is an advantage</li><li>Effective communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Passionate about supporting community programmes and contributing to meaningful, purpose-driven work in a mosque setting.</li></ul><p><strong>Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted within three days after the closing date.</strong></p>",
