    "description": "<p>Darul Ghufran Mosque also known as <em><strong>Menara Biru (Blue Minarent)</strong></em> among the Tampines Residents. </p>  <p>As the community in Tampines flourished, there was a rising need to upgrade the mosque. In September 2016, the Blue Minaret was closed and went through massive upgrading works until March 2019 when it re-opened. During the upgrading period, all activities were carried out at a musolla beside the present site.</p>  <p>It is currently Singapore's lagest mosque with a capacity to hold 5500 people and floor area of 5,910 sq metres. </p> ",
